gomodel:SYNGO_3948  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig1: overexpressed Trio-9, the trio isoform most abundant in the hippocampus increased synaptic AMPAR current amplitude (but not NMDAR) in CA1 pyr. neurons.\nFig2: shRNA-mediated Trio depletion reduces AMPAR current amplitude (but not NMDAR).\nThis phenotype is nearly identical to modulation of Trio's paralog Kalirin. Depletion of both proteins leads to 80% reduction of spines and severely affected AMPAR and NMDAR current amplitudes.. Experimental description: Results 1st paragraph: CA1 pyramidal neurons of organotypic rat hippocampal slice cultures." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2020-07-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3948" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

